768, \"to\": 774}, {\"ngram\": \"this aircraft\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 792}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is also the reason why we called it \\\"The Airplane of Aristotle Onassis.\\\"\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the reason\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 817}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"The Airplane\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 848}, {\"ngram\": \"Aristotle Onassis\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lamda Development, the developers of Hellinikon, honored an agreement signed in May 2023 with the Cultural Center of Olympic Aviation Employees to showcase the historic aircraft.\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 1051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 910, \"end\": 920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elliniko\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hellinikon\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elliniko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elliniko\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Lamda Development\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 890}, {\"ngram\": \"the developers\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 906}, {\"ngram\": \"an agreement\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 942}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"the Cultural Center\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 986}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic Aviation Employees\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1016}, {\"ngram\": \"the historic aircraft\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In July 1956, the Greek State signed an agreement withOnassis, for the exclusive use of air transport in Greece.\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1071, \"end\": 1076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.999956122711801, \"rank\": 4.348417898119554e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.995182448602758, \"rank\": 0.004840870465248483, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"an agreement withOnassis\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1114}, {\"ngram\": \"the exclusive use\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1137}, {\"ngram\": \"air transport\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1154}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On April 6, 1957, the company was renamed Olympic Airways.\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1208, \"end\": 1223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.054803502542095e-61, \"text\": \"Olympic Airways\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"the company\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1195}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first domestic flight started the same year.\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1273, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first domestic flight\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Generally, Olympic had an upswing on a domestic and international level, as well.\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"an upswing\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1307}, {\"ngram\": \"a domestic and international level\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1345}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, in 1971, a subsidiary airline, Olympic Aviation, was established to serve theGreek islandsmore economically and efficiently, and flights were expanded globally.\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Aviation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympic Aviation\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Aviation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Aviation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1368}, {\"ngram\": \"a subsidiary airline\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1399}, {\"ngram\": \"theGreek islandsmore\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1464}, {\"ngram\": \"flights\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1972, Olympic turned to the important Greece-Australia market, beginning Boeing 707-320 operations between Athens and Sydney twice a week via Bangkok and Singapore.\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1608, \"end\": 1622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_707\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Boeing 707-320\", \"types\": [\"Q11436\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_707\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_707\"}, {\"begin\": 1642, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.5992103410664278e-12, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 1653, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.357951622276899e-15, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 1677, \"end\": 1684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suvarnabhumi_Airport\", \"score\": 0.6773174494818278, \"rank\": 0.4764125754699744, \"text\": \"Bangkok\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suvarnabhumi_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suvarnabhumi_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 1689, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Changi_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.66915028396899e-12, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Changi_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Changi_Airport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"the important Greece-Australia market\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1596}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1973, the death of Onassis' son, Alexander, in a plane crash shocked Greek people, and a new phase began for Olympic Airways.\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1737, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"score\": 0.999477287088193, \"rank\": 0.0004385945535933168, \"text\": \"Alexander\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\"}, {\"begin\": 1773, \"end\": 1785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999953583909194, \"rank\": 4.641630648969991e-06, \"text\": \"Greek people\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.054803502542095e-61, \"text\": \"Olympic Airways\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the death\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"Onassis' son\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1735}, {\"ngram\": \"a plane crash\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"a new phase\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1802}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few months later, Onassis sold all of the OA shares to the Greek state and died in 1975.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1874, \"end\": 1876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.9996434626468372, \"rank\": 0.00033072519734994414, \"text\": \"OA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1891, \"end\": 1896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.999956122711801, \"rank\": 4.348417898119554e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Onassis\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1857}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The year of 1976 was a landmark year in the history of Olympic.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The year\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1930}, {\"ngram\": \"a landmark year\", \"from\": 1943, \"to\": 1958}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1973}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 1984}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The airline passed into Greek government's dominance.\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 2039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2010, \"end\": 2015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.999956122711801, \"rank\": 4.348417898119554e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The airline\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 1997}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same year, the firm obtained the first Boeing 737-200 and created Olympic Catering.\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2083, \"end\": 2097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_737\", \"scor